CRITICS' CHOICE: A MIRACLE, A UNIVERSE SETTLING ACCOUNTS WITH TORTURERS BY 
LAWRENCE WESCHLER (PANTHEON: $22.95; 300 PP.;) 
" . . . brilliantly depicts how in the face of extreme repression, there were 
courageous individuals who pointed the way back to freedom. Weschler 
demonstrates the importance of truth-telling for that journey and for the 
healing of whole societies." Margaret Crahan 
